Nine suspects aged between 32 to 51, including five
police officers and a Home Affairs official 
have been arrested by the Hawks.HAWKS spokesperson Captain Matimba Maluleke said the
suspects were arrested  for alleged
corruption, fraud and smuggling of suspected stolen vehicles out of South
Africa.Maluleke said the arrests are a culmination of a Hawks'
investigative project dubbed Mirror aimed at addressing corrupt officials and
illegal activities which includes, smuggling of suspected stolen vehicles at
